long_desc.thetext:
This problem is related to qx.log.appender.Window and takes place when application tries to close log window. It is necessary that Opera blocks pop-up windows (change "Choose how you to prefer to handle pop-ups" preference to "Block unwanted pop-ups", for example) to see the problem. Use the following code to get the error.

Code snippet:

var btn = new qx.ui.form.Button("Leave application");
btn.setLeft(10);
btn.setTop(10);
btn.addEventListener("execute", function(event) {
    window.location = "http://www.google.com";
}, this);
btn.addToDocument();

@ae: We don't use windows for logging in 0.8 so that this bug is not relevant 
to 0.8.

Changed MS
